ce:section.ce:para:
The morphological properties and microstructures of fabricated materials were examined using SEM and TEM analyses. In the SEM images, FeWO4 exhibited cuboid- or oval-like nanoparticles 11–55 nm in size, whereas g-C3N4 exhibited stacked 2D nanosheet structures (Fig. 6
                        ). Furthermore, the images of the FeWO4/g-C3N4 and NGQD/FWO/CN nanocomposites displayed Fe WO4 nanoparticles loaded onto g-C3N4 nanosheets, indicating that Fe WO4 was well decorated on the 2D g-C3N4 sheets or between them. The TEM image of NGQD/FWO/CN in Fig. 7
                         confirms that aggregated nanosized particles were fixed on the 2D g-C3N4. Moreover, the HRTEM image of the aforementioned material illustrates highly defined crystal features of NGQDs, FeWO4, and g-C3N4. The lattice intervals of 0.212, 0.326, 0.375, and 0.472 nm were associated with the (100) facet of graphite, (002) facet of g-C3N4, (011) facet of FeWO4, and the (100) facet of the FeWO4, correspondingly [6,22,27]. In addition, the mapping results demonstrate the existence of C, N, O, Fe, and W in NGQD/FWO/CN-2.5, suggesting excellent incorporation of the NGQDs, g-C3N4, and FeWO4 in this nanocomposite catalyst.
